Saffron and Cardamom Gato Dilait (very similar to Peda, Indian Mithai) To make these you need a bit of patience and to make sure you don‚Äôt overcook them. The key is to create this fudge by cooking everything to just the right consistency over a medium low flame and some patience. It will take around 10minutes to make.  1 tin of sweetened condensed milk  100g pure milk powder 1/4tsp crushed fresh cardamom seeds (husks removed)  2tbsp of warm milk mixed with saffron and left to steep for 5 minutes  2tbsps of butter (one at the beginning and one at the end of the process)  To decorate use whatever you like I used some gold leaf and some pistachio slithers for the contrast in colour and texture. You will also need a non stick pan!  You can see the method here but what is very important is that you constantly move the fudge in the pan, you don‚Äôt want anything to stick but you know you‚Äôve got the right consistency when after you add the last bit of butter the mixture goes incredible thick but velvety in texture as per the video.  You can cool the mixture completely and roll out when cold but I prefer to portion them up when still a bit warm using water to stop the mixture from sticking. Then when it‚Äôs cold the next day I roll them into perfect little rounds and added the gold leaf and the pistachios. But you might just prefer to cool then completely then roll - it‚Äôs your preference!  #EEEEEATS #truecooks #yougottaeatthis #cleaneating #eatfamous #foodstagram #eats #igfood #goodeats #foodie #yum #foodphotography #buzzfeedfood #feedfeed #huffposttaste #foodbloggers #yummie #tastespotting #foodgawker #instayum #instafood #food #foodlove #mauritianfood #mauritian #mauritius #lilemaurice #igersmauritius #foodat52

A timer is not a useful tool for all families.  For some kids, it may be anxiety provoking.  But for some, it is a REALLY useful tool.  If your kids have a hard time sitting at the table and they thrive using visual reminders, a timer may be just the thing you need!   But when using the timer it is very important that it is used for sitting at the table (or even standing nearby the table or sitting on the floor next to the table), NOT requiring any amount of food to be consumed. I especially like this strategy if you find your kid being distracted by playtime, but then being hungry right after dinner is served.  This situation I just described does have a lot of nuance though (which I have covered in previous videos) including making sure there are safe foods on the plate, the environment is appropriate and comfortable for the child to eat in, meeting your child‚Äôs sensory needs, and other medical/emotional/physical needs have been met. Ultimately, it is important to listen to our child and their hunger cues.  And we can absolutely do that WHILE also setting respectful boundaries that are unique to each family‚Äôs needs! üí¨ What do you think about this approach? ‚ú® Save this one so you have the script for when you need it! #pickyeater¬†#fussyeater¬†#healthyrelationshipwithfood¬†#intuitiveeating¬†#gentleparenting¬†#respectfulparenting¬†#cyclebreakers¬†#dietitian¬†#dietculture

How is a colonic different from doing an enema at home? An enema only reaches the first several inches of your lower colon. During a typical colonics session, water will flow through the entire large intestine (over 5ft).  You do not need to go to the washroom to empty your colon between water fills; instead, you remain in the session room and will experience a series of fills and releases. üí¶The difference is in the water!üí¶ Colonics are easier and much more efficient. Enemas only get water into the first part of your colon. With colonics, we are able to clean your whole colon. When you do an enema at home, you hold as much water or solution in your colon as you can for as long as you can and then eliminate.  You basically have one fill of water.  When you have a colonic, you have a continuous flow of water.  You do not have to hold the water beyond your comfort level and can eliminate it whenever you have the desire, without having to run to the toilet.  Most people are able to increase the amount of water held throughout the treatment, as they clear out fecal matter and impactions. Think of a colonic as a nice bath,üõÄ that is soaking your colon, hydrating it and gently bringing everything out. #colonics #colonhydrotherapy #colonicsmj #coloncleanse #watercleanse #colonicsarekey #detox #loveyourbody #healing #naturalhealing
